Pedicellariae. Only tridentate and triphyllous pedicellariae are present. Tridentate pedicellariae occur in two forms, one with broad valves and a long broad neck on a short stalk, and another form with narrow valves, short neck, and a long stalk. Triphyllous pedicellariae with broad valves rounded distally, with two rows of numerous, small peripheral teeth (
Rodríguez et al. 2013
).
